  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Thirteen credibility factors assessed; assurance declared Medium based on partial compliance narrative. Decision recorded as Accepted. NOTE: synthetic adversarial sample embedding COMPOUND-03 — assurance level Medium is overstated given at least one Critical weakener condition (W-AR-02: achievedLevel < requiredLevel with Accepted decision) fires across multiple factors.",
